Hundreds of residents of Sirimon village in Meru today joined the family of security commentator Mwenda Mbijiwe in a more than 10 km walk in protest. To meet Buuri sub-county deputy county commissioner in efforts to pile pressure on authorities to offer a helping hand in unraveling his disappearance. The residents have vowed to hold similar protests every Wednesday until Mbijiwe is found. The security man disappeared on the 12th of June and his mother Jane Gatwiri claims anonymous sources confided in her, her son is somewhere alive.
